Gunmen have kidnapped a former Commissioner in Adamawa State and demanded N30 million ransom from his family. The gunmen allegedly killed a member of the ex-commissioner’s household and injured some others in the course of taking the ex-commissioner away Sources said Wednesday that Engineer Babangida Idris, a Commissioner for Housing and Urban Planning during the immediate past government (when Senator Jibrilla Bindow was the governor) was kidnapped in the early hours of Tuesday. The sources said the kidnappers had surrounded the home of the victim at Bajabure, in Girei local government area, and shot their way around. They allegedly shot the former Commissioner in the foot and wounded some others around the household before taking him away.   What you probably didn’t know about Peter Obi     24 lawmakers file five allegations against Oyo Deputy…     Buhari urges Senate to confirm Ohiani as ICRC DG   “What is particularly worrisome is that there was also an attack during the last APC primaries when the victim escaped an attack by yet to be identified persons who ended up smashing the victim’s windscreen,” a family member said. The family source said that after a long time of not hearing from the kidnappers, they had reached to the family on phone and asked to be given N30 million for Babangida’s freedom. Confirming the kidnapping of Babangida Idris, the Police Public Relations Officer in Adamawa State, SP Suleiman Nguroje said the police had set machinery in motion to get to the kidnappers and rescue Babangida. He said the state Commissioner of Police, CP Sikiru Akande had personally visited the Babangida family for a direct feel of the situation.